  "system": {
    "description": {
      "value": "<p>You gain proficiency with the poisoner's kit if you do not already have it. With one hour of work using a poisoner's kit and expending 25gp worth of materials, you can create a number of doses of potent nonmagical poison equal to your proficiency bonus. Once applied to a weapon or a piece of ammunition as an action, this poison retains its potency for 1 minute or until you hit with the weapon or ammunition. When a creature takes damage from the coated weapon or ammunition, that creature must succeed on a Constitution (DC = 8 + proficiency bonus + the ability modifier used) saving throw or take a number of d4s equal to your proficiency bonus as poison damage and become poisoned until the end of your next turn.</p>",
